;The Mozilla Leadership Network
Ri ruk'amab'ey poponem pa Mozilla


;Connecting Leaders
Kitunik k'amöl taq b'ey


;The Mozilla Leadership Network is a global network of diverse leaders - from the young activist teaching web literacy to her community, to the executive leading a global organization - who will ensure the next wave of access, inclusion and opportunity online.
Ri kik'amaya'l poponem pa Mozilla jun aj ruwach'ulew chi k'amab'ey jalajoj taq poponela', nitikïr rik'in ri na'ob'alil xtän k'ajol, ri nuk'üt ri ajk'amaya'l pa rutinamit, k'a ri poponel k'amöl rub'ey jun aj ruwach'ulew moloj, ri xkejikib'an ri jun chik rucholajem pa ruwi' okem, nimilem chuqa' samaj pa k'amab'ey.


;Leaders in this network will take action together to:
Ri k'amöl taq rub'ey re k'amab'ey re' xkesamäj junam richin:


;Shape and spread the open internet agenda;
Tinuk' chuqa' titalüx ri jaqäl cholb'äl ruq'ij r K'amaya'l;


;Model ‘open’ values and practices in institutions, products and policies around the world.
K'amb'äl tzij ‘tijaq’ taq rejqalem chuqa' rusamajixik pa taq moloj, taq tikojil chuqa' taq na'ojil chi jun ri ruwach'ulew.


;How we work
Achike rub'eyal yojsamäj


;The Mozilla Leadership Network accomplishes its work through thematic ‘hubs,’ communities of people with diverse expertise, who are helping others build the capacity to advance the open Internet in their field or topic of interest.
Ri Ruk'amab'ey poponem Mozilla nub'än ri rusamaj kik'in ri taq ‘ruk'u'x,’ ruk'u'x taq na'oj, ajtinamït taq winäq ri jalajöj ketamab'al, ri yekito' ch'aqa' chik pa ruwi' ketamab'al richin nikisamajij ri jaqäl K'amaya'l pa ri kik'ojlemal o ruk'u'x na'oj nikajo'.


;Our current hubs include:
Ri taq qasamajay kik'wan:


;<a href="%(url_learning)s">Learning.</a> Educators and librarians committed to transforming learning in our digital age.
<a href="%(url_learning)s">Etamanem.</a> Tijonela' chuqa' taq ajwujib'äl kiya'on kik'u'x rik'in ri ruch'ojmirisaxik etamab'äl pa ri na'ob'alil qaramaj.


;<a href="%(url_science)s">Science.</a> Researchers and data scientists committed to making research and practice more open.
<a href="%(url_science)s">Etamab'äl.</a> Ajkanonela' chuqa' taq ajna'oj kichin taq tzij kan xkiya' kitzij richin junelïk jaqäl ri rukanoxik na'oj chuqa' ri samaj.


;<a href="%(url_advocacy)s">Internet Policy & Advocacy.</a> Individuals and organizations focused on advancing open Internet issues.
<a href="%(url_advocacy)s">Runa'ojil K'amaya'l chuqa' Kolonem.</a> Winaqi' chuqa' taq moloj nikiya' kitzub'al chi rij kisamajixik jaqäl taq ruk'u'x na'oj pa K'amab'ey.


;<a href="%(url_women)s">Women & Web Literacy.</a> Community organizers and senior leaders creating opportunities for women and girls to develop web literacy skills.
<a href="%(url_women)s">Women & Web Literacy.</a> Ri ajtinamït taq moloj chuqa' nimaläj taq poponela' yekitz'ük taq samaj richin chi ri xtani' chuqa' ixoqi' tik'oje' ketamab'al richin choltz'ib'anem pan Ajk'amaya'l.


;<a href="%(url_iot)s">Internet of Things.</a> Hackers and designers creating provocative prototypes for what an open Internet of Things could and should be.
<a href="%(url_iot)s">Kik'amaya'l wachinäq.</a> Kematz'ib'il taq poqonanela' chuqa' ri taq ajwachib'äl ri yekinük' nab'ey taq ruwäch ri nikib'än jun jaqäl Kik'amaya'l wachinäq ri k'o ta chi ke ri'.


;Our Initiatives
Tikirib'äl taq qasamaj


;The Mozilla Leadership Network pursues our goals through five key initiatives, which are reflected in each hub:
Ri Ruk'amab'ey rupoponem Mozilla yekitzeqelb'ej ri taq qarayb'al rik'in wo'o' ruk'u'x tikirib'äl taq samaj, ri yeq'alajin pa ri taq qasamajay:


;<em>Curricula & Training.</em> We provide free and open curricula and training programs to help leaders develop the skills they need to ensure the next wave of access, inclusion and opportunity online. Example: <a href="%(url_weblit_module)s">Web Literacy Training Module</a>
<em>Curricula & Training.</em> Niqaya' sipan chuqa' jaqäal taq cholk'ut chuqa' taq runuk'samaj tijonïk richin yeto' ri k'amöl taq b'ey chi kekisamajij ri ketamab'al nik'atzin chi ke richin jun chik peraja okem, nimoj chuqa' samaj pa k'amab'ey. Tz'etb'äl:<a href="%(url_weblit_module)s">Web Literancy Training Module</a>


;<em>Partnerships.</em> We initiate and grow partnerships that enable Mozilla, our community and our allies to maximize their impact. Example: <a href="%(url_gigabit)s">Gigabit Community Fund</a>
<em>Partherships.</em> Xqatikirisaj chuqa' xeqanük' taq ichinmoloj, ri nikiya' q'ij chi re ri Mozilla, ri qatinamit chuqa' ri e qato'öy nikinimirisaj ri ruchuq'a'. Tz'etb'äl: <a href="%(url_gigabit)s"> Gigabit Community Fund</a>


;<em>Convening.</em> We bring members of the Mozilla Leadership Network together, to learn from one another, exchange ideas and join forces. Example: <a href="%(url_mozFest)s">MozFest</a>
<em>Convening.</em> Yeqamöl ri e k'o chupam ri Ruk'amab'ey rupoponem Mozilla richin chi qakojol niqetamaj, yeqajunamaj taq na'oj chuqa' niqatün quchuq'a'. Tz'etb'äl: <a href="%(url_mozFest)s">MozFest</a>


;<em>Membership.</em> Members join because they share Mozilla’s vision, and stay because of the strong, diverse community and unique professional development opportunities the network provides. Example: <a href="%(url_fellowships)s">Fellowships</a>
<em>Membership.</em> Ri qawinaq nikitün pe ki' ruma koqan ri rutzub'al Mozilla chuqa' yek'oje' chupam ruma ri nïm chuqa' jalajöj tinamït chuqa' ri junilal taq samaj pa ruwi' ruk'iyirisanem retamab'al winäq nusüj ri k'amab'ey. Tz'etb'äl: <a href="%(url_fellowships)s">Fellowships</a>


